Class CssTableView

java.lang.Object
  com.habitsoft.kiyaa.views.CssTableView
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesChangeEvents, View
public class CssTableView
extends Object
implements View, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesChangeEvents

A "CSS" table view. The assumption is that you are doing layout using the "grid" system and thus you don't want to use

tags because the browser doesn't obey your commands when you do so. Each column must be given a CSS class which specifies its width. In addition, the classes .thead, .tbody, .tr, .th, and .td are added to the appropriate div tags within the layout, so they can be styled using css.
